<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="3" unit="words"/><date when="1881-08-27">August 27<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1881</date></p>
<lb/><ab rend="gray"><space extent="5" unit="words"/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/><add place="inspace" hand="#U">C129/129</add></ab>
<lb/><p>Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="3" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>With reference to your
<lb/>letter to me informing me that you
<lb/>have obtained a situation in the
<lb/><orgName>Railway &amp; Metropolitan Omnibus C<hi rend="sup">oy.</hi></orgName>
<lb/>I beg to say that I have handed <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>
<lb/>Beale</persName> a sum of two pounds to enable you
<lb/>to purchase clothes as you suggest. This
<lb/>money has been sent to me by <persName>M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi> Nichol</persName>
<lb/>with a request that I would appropriate
<lb/>it for your benefit as I might
<lb/>consider best. I am glad that it is
<lb/>available for you just at the moment
<lb/>when you are apparently able to turn it
<lb/>to the best account. <space extent="1" unit="chars"/>It is however necesry
<lb/>for me to tell you that I know of no
<lb/>quarter from which further assistance is likely
<lb/>to be obtained. Please send me a note which
<lb/><seg rend="small">I may communicate to <persName>M<hi rend="sup">rs</hi> Nichol</persName></seg> <space extent="1" unit="words"/><persName>F.W.C.</persName></p>
			</div>
